# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker / Replit deployment ignore.
#
# Heavy runtime assets live in Replit Object Storage and are streamed by
# server/cdnFallback.ts (see replit.md → "Asset Pipeline"). At deploy time the
# entire `public/` tree is stripped from the image — the running server creates
# `public/avatars/` and `public/textures/ground/` on demand for the avatar
# cache and Poly Haven sync.
#
# `node_modules/` is also stripped so the deploy build reinstalls only what
# package.json declares (the dev tree contains many never-used packages from
# earlier experiments — minecraft-data, phaser, cesium, babylon, etc).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Version control — biggest single win (~8.6 GB, includes Git LFS)
.git/
.gitattributes
.gitignore

# Local node_modules (~2.9 GB) — Replit deploy reinstalls from package.json
node_modules/

# Heavy assets (~2.4 GB) — streamed from Replit Object Storage in production
public/

# Agent / workspace tooling not needed at runtime (~140 MB)
.local/
.agents/
.replit_db_*
.upm/
.breakpoints
.config/
.cache/
.pythonlibs/
generated-icon.png

# Build & language-server caches
node_modules/.cache/
node_modules/.vite/
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo
.eslintcache

# Editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Logs & temp
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
tmp/
.tmp/

# Dev-only tools (~99 MB) — ROYGBIV editor side workflow
tools/roygbiv/
tools/inspect-dwarf.mjs

# Source maps in production bundle (saves ~30% of bundle size)
dist/public/assets/*.map

# Docs (~36 KB, but no need at runtime)
docs/

# Build script source (already compiled into dist/)
script/buildhammer/

# Misc loose files
screenshots/
puter-sprite-app/
CONSOLIDATION_NOTES.md
CLOUDFLARE_DEPLOY.md
